    <measure>Number of Subjects Achieving Clinical Response</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline to 8 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>Clinical response is defined as a decrease in the total modified Mayo score from baseline of ≥3 or a ≥30% decrease in the total modified Mayo score from baseline, along with a decrease in the rectal bleeding score ≥1 or an absolute rectal bleeding score ≤1 at Week 8.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Number of Subjects Achieving Clinical Remission</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline to 8 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>Clinical remission is defined as a total modified Mayo score ≤2 with no individual score &gt;1 at Week 8.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Change From Baseline in Total Modified Mayo Score</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline to 8 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>A modified Mayo score was used to evaluate disease activity using 4 components, including stool frequency, rectal bleeding, endoscopy, and physician assessment. Components = Stool frequency score 0-3 (normal- &gt;4 stools/day more than normal), rectal bleeding score 0-3 (none-passing blood alone), mucosal appearance at endoscopy 0-3 (normal-severe disease), physician rating of disease activity 0-3 (normal-severe). The total Modified Mayo score ranges from 0 to 12, with higher scores indicating greater disease severity.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
